        "title": "check reference class type at compile time",
        "body": "<p>If I have some type declarations like:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>JCheckBoxMenuItem t1;\nJRadioButtonMenuItem t2;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>and then a method like<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>addItem(JMenuItem i)\n{\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>can I know if <code>i<\/code> is a <code>JCheckBoxMenuItem<\/code> or a <code>JRadioButtonMenuItem<\/code> type without having\nan instance of them when I call it with <code>addItem(t1)<\/code> or <code>addItem(t2)<\/code> ???<\/p>\n",
